- Open Server Manager
- Add role "Remote desktop services" with services
  - Remote Desktop Session Host
  - remote Desktop Licensing
- Select
- "Do not require Network level authentication"
   - Licening Mode: configure later
   - Finish installation

It will reboot server, once server is back up

Go to


Administrative Tools >> remote desktop services >> Remote desktop licensing manager

Right click on server name, and click on "Activate Server"

```diagram

```

- Wizard will open
  - click on next
  - Connection method: Automatic
    - Enter name: Peter Cruz
    - Company: Serverpoint
    - Country: US
    - email: support@serverpoint.com
    - Organizational unit: CS
    - Address: Las Vegas
    - City: Las Vegas
		- Sate: NV
		- Postal code 89000
		- Click next
- Then check "Start install licenses wizard now"
- Click next

On next wizard

- Select
  - License program: Service provider license agreement
- Click next
   - Enter our Microsoft licensing number (can be obtained from product key spread sheet in gmail)
- Click next
  - Product Version: windows 2008 or windows server 2008 R2
  - license type: TS or RDS per user CAL
  - Quantity: enter the number of licenses customer want, ex: 5
- click next then finish

Then Go to Administrative Tools >> remote desktop services >> Remote desktop session host configuration

Right click on Remote desktop licensing mode >> properties

```diagram

```

Select "per user"

click on "Add" button under "Specified license servers"

```diagram

```

In new windows, Select "Local" server, and click on Add button
Then press OK

```diagram

```

Click apply button, then OK


Now log off from Windows, and login again, and License will start working.
